Liverpool FC has beaten fellow Premier League side, Tottenham 2 – 0 to win 2019 European Champions League. Second minute penalty goal by Egyptian forward, Mohammed Salah and a late goal by Divock Origi handed the reds their first European triumph since 2005. The Jurgen Klop coached side which had lost to Spanish giants Real Madrid in last season’s final made amends in the keenly contested match at the Spanish capital, Madrid on Saturday. 